### 4. Find First Occurrence of an Element

**Problem:** Find the first occurrence of a key in an array.

```java
class FirstOccurrence {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {2, 4, 4, 4, 6, 8};
        int key = 4;
        int index = -1;

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] == key) {
                index = i;
                break;
            }
        }
        System.out.println("First occurrence index: " + index);
    }
}
```

---

### 5. Find Last Occurrence of an Element

**Problem:** Find the last occurrence of a key in an array.

```java
class LastOccurrence {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 3, 3, 4};
        int key = 3;
        int index = -1;

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] == key)
                index = i;
        }
        System.out.println("Last occurrence index: " + index);
    }
}
```

---

### 6. Count Occurrences of an Element

**Problem:** Count how many times a key appears in an array.

```java
class CountOccurrences {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {5, 1, 5, 3, 5, 7};
        int key = 5;
        int count = 0;

        for (int num : arr) {
            if (num == key)
                count++;
        }
        System.out.println("Count: " + count);
    }
}
```

---

### 7. Search in Unsorted Array

**Problem:** Search an element in an unsorted array.

```java
class SearchUnsortedArray {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {9, 2, 7, 4, 1};
        int key = 4;
        boolean found = false;

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] == key) {
                System.out.println("Element found at index: " + i);
                found = true;
                break;
            }
        }

        if (!found)
            System.out.println("Element not found");
    }
}
```

